1. Purpose

IX-IntentRealityLoop is made source-available so that interested parties may
inspect the project, review its technical structure, and perform limited
noncommercial evaluation to decide whether to contact the copyright holder about
a separate commercial or operational license.

IX-IntentRealityLoop is a research prototype and source-available evaluation
runtime for governed sensorimotor agency loops. It is intended to explore how
a cognition system can bind user request, interpretation, choice, permission,
bounded action, feedback, memory update, and replayable evidence without
self-authorizing or overclaiming capability.

IX-IntentRealityLoop is not represented as artificial general intelligence,
certified artificial general intelligence, independently validated AGI, a
complete AGI system, a consciousness system, a self-authorizing autonomy system,
production-ready autonomy, safety-certified software, security-certified
software, robotics-certified software, medical-device software, BCI-certified
software, procurement-ready software, or software approved for live physical
actuation, unsupervised operational decision-making, or real-world deployment.

This license does not grant open-source rights. It does not grant permission for
commercial use, production use, redistribution, modification, derivative works,
hosted-service use, resale, procurement use, contractor use, agency operational
use, government operational use, live physical actuation, clinical use, medical
use, BCI use, assistive-device deployment, robotics deployment, or any use
intended to generate revenue, operational advantage, procurement advantage, or
deployed capability unless a separate written agreement is executed with Bryce
Lovell.

